â­ï¸Deep condition! on the days I do a clarifying wash I always deep condition! Iâve been loving the honey miracle mask @tginatural

â­ï¸Be nice to your hair: satin pillow cases, silk bonnets/scarves and satin scrunchies WORK! The amount of breakage I used to have from regular hair ties was criminal! 
â­ï¸Be a gentle brusher. Between wash days I only detangle my hair if I am oiling it or I wait until Iâm in the shower. This made a huge difference in curls longevity!

These true armadillo lizards almost NEVER do this in captivity. In the wild balling up like this is their defense mechanism, but in over two years of keeping these captive bred lizards in captivity Iâve only see it a couple times. I had to remove him to clean out his enclosure, and for whatever reason this spooked him for a minute. He went back to normal shortly after. I never try to get them to ball up on purpose as Iâm sure this is stressful for them. No I canât help you get one eitherð do your research and find breeders, which can be hard to come by! This is the true armadillo lizard Ouroborus cataphractus- not the forest armadillo lizard you can find for $60 at a pet shop. The site that comes up if you google them for sale is based in France and a SCAM. No breeders need to post these for sale since there is a waitlist and they cost many thousands of dollars for a baby. If you see one for sale on a website itâs a scam. Have to add that last part since I get asked about it every time I post these guys!

Tanghulu in less than 5 mins! ð

** FYI, the sugar and the dipping containers get SUPER hot because youâre microwaving this for a few mins. Make sure to use protective gear*! 

Serving size: 1 
 
-4 tbsp sugar
-2 tbsp water
-washed and fully dried fruit of choice

Steps: 
1. Add the sugar into a heat safe vessel and add the water. DONT stir. 
2. Place into a microwave and microwave on 30 second increments until the sugar dissolves and turns an amber color. DO NOT mix or stir the sugar between microwave increments! This disturbs the crystallization
